                                RexxMast

        Must be running in order for programs that use the AREXX language
to operate properly. 

        A command to start Rexxmast is part of the standard
Startup-Sequence (the file that is read when the Amiga is turned on or
rebooted). You only need to open the RexxMast icon if you remove the
RexxMast command from your Startup-sequence or if your computer doesn't
have enough memory to load the program. RexxMast is explained in full on
Fred Fish disk. Contact a PD company.


